title: Crash and Burn
short_desc: The crew desperately try to find a planet to subdue an enraged squoatling.

content.text: t!8ball Does Emmett go into the kitchen for look for some food?
ðŸŽ± | My sources say no, Zander.
t!8ball Does Sanya walk around the ship?
ðŸŽ± | Cannot predict now, Brakia.
So, Emmett, where to next?
t!8ball Does Sanya walk to the lounge?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, definitely, Brakia.
Emmett is lounging around the sofa idly, frowning.
I'm pooped, really.
Been feeling kind-of down for a few days.
Seth side-eyes the hallway.
Our other elf went to bed...
Hmmmm, how about... somewhere green?
t!8ball Is Chomsky caught by Sanya cradling a small flame in a cup of alcohol?
ðŸŽ± | Don't count on it, PlasmaPerson.
Do you guysss...
Sanya quieted down, trying to think of the right words to say.
With lots of plants..
Do you guysss ever... feel dread?
KYL300 disconnects from its charging station.
I have not felt it yet, though I know the feeling.
I'm feeling dread right now, man...
Emmett flickers his tongue out in boredom.
I know you know, robot.
Do we have any leftover grass?
Can we just go somewhere with nothing but plants... and maybe some good sights...
I haven't had some in a few days...
Jim shrugs.
I don't know, just somewhere fresh.
That sounds nice.
Nothing to worry about, no one trying to kill us, just relaxation.
Emmett takes a deep breath and limps over the couch arm, feeling the effects of grass withdrawal.
Seth. I need your stash to even function.
I'm dying here.
t!8ball Does Seth take bring out fifteen very attractive women?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, definitely, Bagelwrecker.
Seth snaps his fingers, an array of hot ladies appearing behind him.
Here is my stash.
Emmett weakly smacks his face in frustration.
Not your women!
Where did you keep all thossse?
Jim gasps at the hot women.
What? Why and how?
t!8ball Does Matthias finally wake up from a deep and cold sleep?
ðŸŽ± | My sources say yes, Enchantingtable2013.
They live in my room.
Amazingly my room has a basement thing.
Seth smirks, possibly harboring even more women in his basement.
t!8ball Does Kyle run a scan on the women?
ðŸŽ± | Signs point to yes, ProfessorTree.
Five of those women have at least one STD.
Seth shrugs and looks back at his harem.
I haven't had the chance to get them a cure.
t!8ball Are all the women alive?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, TheBlade.
Some of the womens' heads move a bit mechanically, falling limp.
They don't look so well...
That's cause' some of them are robots.
Seth flicks one of the robots' faces.
Why would anyone want a mate that doesssn't have real blood?
t!8ball Does Emmett fall from his seat due to "exhaustion"?
ðŸŽ± | My sources say no, Zander.
Mammals tend to crave sex.
I seriously need something...
Emmett scratches at his cheeks in agony.
They're servant bots...
Seth stares at his son, frowning for just a second at his demeanor.
Go check under my bed Emmett.
They sometimes enslave other species to pleasure themselves sexually...
Despite speaking in a factual tone, the KYL unit appears to have a judgmental stance, its hands on its hips.
Fine, fine.
t!8ball Does Sanya get food?
ðŸŽ± | It is decidedly so, Brakia.
Sanya stands from her chair.
I hunger. I'm getting a sssnack. Anyone want something?
t!8ball Foes Chomsky get out of the random room he slept in last episode and join the others?
ðŸŽ± | Signs point to yes, PlasmaPerson.
Emmett eyeballs Sanya, his head upside down from the couch arm.
Plant person--er, Sanya. Do you happen to grow grass on you?
Chomsky nods as he enters the lounge.
Yo'.
Hey.
Chomsky points finger guns at KYL300.
No, I don't grow grasss on myssself.
Emmett sighs.
Exactly, because grass doesn't grow on grass!
Chomsky winks.
Heh.
Emmett groans from Chomsky's comment.
Shut up, pyro.
Emmett slowly gets up from the sofa, heading to Seth's room.
I'll be in Seth's room, if you need me.
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.
Or anything he would do...
Mhm.
t!8ball Does Seth go through the joint bank account?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, Bagelwrecker.
HEY! Emmett, we're broke!
We need a mission.
Good idea.
Emmett was cautiously digging under Seth's bed, trying to find some grass.
MMh mhmh mhmhh m mmh!
Broke? what did you wassste all your money on?
My guess is food and hookers.
Food, fuel, ammo, repairs, and hookers.
Emmett feels something slimy on his hoof and jumps in surprise, his horns hitting the bottom of the bed.
Fuck!
Would you like me to search for any jobs in the area?
Emmett groans and shakes his hoof furiously.
I got condom on my hands!
I wouldn't mind it.
We could always rob a place...
Chomsky snickers.
Seth folds his arms in disapproval.
We could always not.
t!8ball Does Kyle search for jobs in the area?
ðŸŽ± | My reply is no, ProfessorTree.
We have too many tickets already, no need to bring more attention to that.
Emmett throws a bunch of Seth's stuff out from beneath the bed in a panic.
THERE'S NO GRASS!
Uh oh...
t!8ball Does Emmett sluggishly get back to the lounge?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, definitely, Zander.
Guys, lets just find a green planet.
With grass.
Would I have to leave my flamethrower on the ship?
Depends on where we go.
Emmett falls face first onto the couch. He speaks, his voice muffled.
Seth, I need you to drive.
Unless you go by a small forest.... JUST A SMALL ONE!
I gotcha.
Without question, Seth heads to the cockpit, grabbing another box labelled, "ONE-TIME HACK".
You will have to leave it.
I see. Hm. Too bad.
Sanya gives Jim and Chomsky a disgusted expression.
If you're dissscusssing dessstroying a foressst, I'm not okay with that.
Emmett groans.
It's not like it's your forest...
Sanya balls up her fists.
ALL flora mattersss to me!
Emmett refuses to raise his head, his voice still muffled.
Chomps got a point...
Sanya tilts her head in confusion.
Chompsss?
Chomsky furrows his brow.
Who you calling Chomps?
Emmett relaxes his shoulders.
I don't think I have the strength to tell you.
t!8ball Does Sanya sit on the couch, eating a clump of raw meat?
ðŸŽ± | It is certain, Brakia.
Sanya sits on the couch, managing to forget about Emmett. She sits on Emmett's back, who just depresses beneath her body.
Lets just get there and find out, ok?
Jim looks around in concern.
Also, has anyone seen my Guinea Pig?
Chomsky recalls seeing bones in the kitchen trash at one point in time.
Sanya ate it...
What?!
Chomsky shrugs apathetically.
Whoops.
Seth yells from across the ship.
You mean Lotus?
Sanya?! WHAT DID YOU DO?!
Jim's hands shake as he tries to grab Sanya, who manages to dodge him.
That was a guinea pig? Why was it in the fridge?
Oh...
Jim puts his hands down and sighs in relief.
KYL walks over to Seth, ignoring Jim and Sanya's predicament.
We should get to a flora-filled planet...
Ok, not the guinea pig then.
Emmett feels Sanya's weight shift, causing him to feel some discomfort.
If you're going to sit on me, at least sit near my legs...
Garrick emerges, hearing Emmett's pleas and taking them the wrong way.
What?!
Chomsky puts a hand on Jim's shoulder.
Did you check the engine room? Its warm in there.
What?
Jim makes an absurd look over to Chomsky.
For Thelma?
Yes.
I could probably scan from here...
KYL300 sets up its scanning module and looks about the ship for Thelma.
Garrick ignores Emmett and involves himself in Jim's plight.
What's Thelma?
My guinea pig...
Jim frowns.
t!8ball Is Themla found in the scorching hot engine room?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook good, PlasmaPerson.
KYL finishes his scanning and gives Jim a thumbs up.
OH JESUS CHRIST, SHE'S IN THE ENGINE ROOM, ISN'T SHE?!
Jim runs to the engine room in terror.
I hear little screaming!
Chomsky follows Jim.
Seth speaks into his comms watch.
We need heatsinks in the engine room I guess...
I hear everything!
Garrick phases into the engine room.
GET HER OUT OF THERE!!
Jim tries to rescue his pet but upon entering the room, he jumps back, the temperature scorching hot as Seth pilots the ship.
It seems like it's on fire!
Woah, really?!
Garrick circles a finger on the side of his head, signifying that KYL300 is Captain Obvious.
I don't think ssshe'sss gonna sssurvive...
Sanya looks over from the couch, watching smoke erupt from the engine room.
Chomsky watches Jim try to enter the room.
She's your rodent...
It'll be fine.
Garrick pokes the burning Themla.
Chomsky, you have fireproof clothes, right?!
If ssshe doesssn't, Can I ea-
The others look at Sanya disapprovingly.
Keep her?
Chomsky glares at Sanya.
Yeah. I do.
GET THE FUCK IN THERE!
AND GET HER OUT!
Fine.
Chomsky scoffs and enters the engine room to grab the guinea pig.
Okay, but...
What does guinea pig taste like?
t!8ball Does Matthias stare at his hand and view a brand?
ðŸŽ± | Without a doubt, Enchantingtable2013.
Emmett is still muffled, and nearly pukes.
Barf.
Jim faces Garrick in disapproval.
Garrick, they are tinder and are soft at the same time...
Chomsky grabs the burning rodent with his fireproof gloves. He heads back to Jim and hands her Themla.
Here you go.
Matthias flips his hand repeatedly, in awe of the brand.
Woah...
t!8ball Does Seth pilot the ship to a primitive forest planet?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, Bagelwrecker.
The rodent stops moving, still engulfed in flames.
She's a little burnt.
It's on fire, Chonky!
Sanya breathes in the fumes, enjoying the smell of smoked meat.
Yeah, I think sshe'ss dead...
Jim's mouth quivers. He doesn't care that his hands are burning from holding his dearly departed pet.
Oh my god, Themla...
This thing is kinda cool, especially when it glows...
Matthias makes a fist, the brand glowing even brighter.
t!8ball Is Thelma alive?
ðŸŽ± | My sources say no, TheBlade.
Chomsky smothers the flames on Thelma, her body lifeless and scorched.
Emmett squirms beneath Sanya, his weakened body in no state to push her off of him.
Sanya, get your plant butt off of me.
Jim falls to his knees dramatically, screaming to the roof while holding the rodent corpse.
NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!
Garrick, again, takes note of Emmett's pleas.
Woah. What's going on between you two?
WHY CRUEL WORLD!?!
Yeah, ssshe'ss dead. Can I sssee her?
Sanya holds her hands out for Themla's body, not bothering to stand up.
It's okay, that's how you deal with a living being in fire.
Emmett tries to pick himmself up to no avail.
You are extremely heavy for a plant!
She'll be fine...
Chomsky stares at Themla's body apathetically.
I wonder what such a cool tattoo can do...
Matthias gets up, still staring at his branded hand.
Jim shakes with rage at Sanya's euphemisms for eating his pet.
Sanya, I will personaly throw you back in that cell if you touch her.
Sanya leans back fromm Jim's threat.
What?
Sanya finally notices Emmett underneath her. She is mortified by using Emmett as a chair.
OH MY GOD!
How heavy are plant people normally...?
Jim grumbles.
About 147 pounds.
t!choose a primitive forest planet | a high-tech forest planet | a war planet cloaked as a forest planet
ðŸ¤” | ProfessorTree, I pick a war planet cloaked as a forest planet!
Garrick, surprised by how heavy a plant could be, squeals.
E!
Alright, we're going logging.
Seth redirects the ship to head to the aforementioned war planet cloaked as a forest planet.
I give up...
Emmett stops squirming and sighs loudly.
Sanya gasps at the prospect of chopping wood on a potentially untouched planet.
We better not be!
Jim pinches his brow.
How about, no touching the plants, we go bury Themla, and Emmett gets some grass?
Spread the ashes...
Jim eyeballs the cockpit.
No touching the plants, especially for you, Seth.
Nah, I got a better idea...
Seth smirks.
Garrick takes out a rubber mallet from his pockets and makes a swinging motion, confusing the mallet for an axe.
You can't stop me!
Sanya shifts her weight intentionally to be annoying.
Get the ass off of me!!
In all ways, Seth!
No touching!
Chomsky frowns a bit, now feeling guilty for Themla's demise.
I'll get you a new one.
t!8ball Does Seth make a Thelma Stew?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, Bagelwrecker.
But you're a good chair...
Sanya pets Emmett's head to his chagrin.
Oh.
Seth laughs ferociously.
That's a fetish in Emmett's culture.
Emmett holds his face, having been reminded by some forms of Squoatopian media Seth shown him in the past.
This is embarrassing...
Sanya looks at Emmett in mild disgust.
I did not know that.
KYL300 tilts its head.
Is the crew always this dysfunctional?
I'll get off...
Jim cringes.
That's a fetish in many cultures..
Garrick turns to Kyle.
Yeah.
Chomsky shrugs, taking off his gloves.
I dunno. I've only been here a week, but so far yeah.
t!8ball Does Sanya get off of Emmett?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook not so good, RPretribution.
Emmett mumbles, defeated.
Just move to my legs please...
Alright.
Sanya, instead of getting off of Emmett like she said she would, stays in place.
t!8ball Does the crew reach the planet?
ðŸŽ± | It is certain, Zander.
As the ship enters the atmosphere, Jim stares the ship's sensors, irked by how peaceful forest is.
Something doesn't seem right...
t!8ball Does Sanya get off Emmett yet?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, Brakia.
Well, you guys can stay here.
Emmett, still weakened by his grass withdrawals, is starting to get pissed by Sanya's humor.
Move to my flipping legs, woman!
Have fun.
Garrick heads away from the couch duo.
Jim stares out a window, looking about the forest's flora below with his cybernetic eye.
These plants are not habitable together... at least, not that close to each other.
Something doesn't seem right.
Something's off...
Seth stomps over to Sanya and Emmett and screams at the two of them, tired of their antics.
JUST FUCK ALREADY!
If it's wrong, burn it down.
Chomsky smiles like a giddy child by this thought.
Emmett sighs, not caring about the plants' relationship to one another.
JIM, I NEED MY GRASS!
Garrick makes a disgusted face over what he was hearing.
Oh.
We need to leave. NOW.
KYL heads over to the cockpit in a panic.
Seth flings his arms forward with each word.
JUST EAT HER ASS!
Just get out of the ship, we've landed.
Something's off, and it's not Sanya.
Emmett looks over his shoulder up at Sanya and questions softly.
Is her ass made of grass?
Sanya's face contorts in a fury over Seth's demands.
COULD YOU SSSHUT UP, SSSETH!
Jim takes one look at Seth and rolls his eyes.
I think, the only thing ON is Seth.
Garrick giggles.
Eat Sanya grass!
Not yet...
Seth winks.
Sanya lightly pushes Emmett's head down.
Don't touch my butt.
KYL checks the ships sensors and compares it with an air quality scanner.
This atmosphere is much too polluted to hold this much plant life...
Eat Sanya!
Garrick takes out a plastic utensil set.
We need to get out of here...
Mmmm, no thanks.
Seth heads to the ship's entrance with confidence.
SANYA SALAD!
Garrick edges closer to Sanya, licking his lips.
Lets press forward!
Sanya isnt even edible, in any way. Most of her is actually poisons.
SHUT UP GARLIC!
Sanya smacks the plastic spork and knife from Garrick's hands.
For glory and my cock!
Emmett has completely given up at this point.
Let me flip over, at least!
Land the ship already! I wanna see what's going on.
Seth, this planet isn't what it seems...
Kyle sounds nervous.
Fine!
Sanya gets up to allow Emmett to flip over. He does so while taking a deep breath. Sanya decides to sit back down on him, actually finding her spot comfortable at this point.
I'M GOING TO LOG AND YOU CANT STOP ME!
Seth grabs an axe from the array of tools mmounted on the wall near the hatch.
How is Emmett even breathing...?
Garrick watches as Emmett manages to breath normally despite his chest being depressed.
t!8ball Does everyone inn the ship get out to investigate the strange planet?
ðŸŽ± | Don't count on it, PlasmaPerson.
Emmett takes in Garrick's statement and thinks for a moment, questioning how he is able to breathe so well despite the floran's weight.
Are you like excreting oxygen or something?
Me? I don't know.
Sanya shrugs.
t!8ball Does the crew land and exit the ship?
ðŸŽ± | It is decidedly so, Bagelwrecker.
We'll never get anywhere this way...
Garrick maintains his interest in the plant and her goat seat.
Emmett looks away, trying to find some good in the world through his fragile state.
That's kinda cool, if you are...
We need to get away from this planet, Seth.
Garrick rolls his eyes, getting a bit irritated by Kyle repeating itself.
Then let's go, what're we waiting for?
Kyle decides to go against the captain of the ship, sitting in the pilot's seat to drag the crew away from the potentially dangerous planet.
Seth, I'm taking the wheel.
Jim frowns, having wanted to explore the dangerous forest.
Emmett looks uncomfortable.
I think you're more bearable now. I guess.
t!8ball Does Kyle successfully pilot the ship away from the planet?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook not so good, ProfessorTree.
Garrick attempts to push KYL300 out of the pilot's seat despite having no piloting prowess.
I'll pilot the ship.
Seth, having followed Kyle, actually shoves him out of the seat.
Fuck off, bastard.
Garrick grins wildly.
It'll be fine!
Why are we going away from the planet?!
I'm great at piloting!
Kyle gets up, unfazed by Seth's aggressiveness.
This planet is unsafe.
Who cares!
t!8ball Does an unidentified ship start coming towards the crew's location?
ðŸŽ± | It is certain, TheBlade.
Guys...
Jim points at a ship heading towards them in the distance.
What is that?
Seth, Kyle, and Garrick head back out the Polonot.
It's a ship.
I'll scan it.
KYL300 starts to get a scan on the ship and is left speechless for a moment.
How about we just ignore it instead?
Seth takes out his axe and flips it around haphazardly.
Because I don't care.
Kyle stops scanning the ship.
Oh, fuck!
Sanya, could you pass me that bottle over there?
Emmett points at a bottle of space rum on the endtable.
That's a Mantis warlord dropship.
Uh, Sssure.
Sanya, having taken out a book to read, hands Emmett his drink.
Mmmmm... Mantis.
Seth smiles brightly.
Been a while since I had mantis stew.
t!8ball Does Garrick fly around aimlessly?
ðŸŽ± | It is decidedly so, RPretribution.
Manti are some of the most dangerous races known...
Chomsky clearly does not take the hint, having never heard of the Manti.
Mantis warlord?
We need to get the hell out of here!
Garrick stops flying around aimlessly.
Then let's go.
Jeez.
Seth groans and heads further out into the forest.
They're also the tastiest.
And I'm hungry.
Chomsky, liking Seth's tone, takes out his flamemthrower psychotically.
They sound BURNABLE!
As if controlled by peer pressure, Garrick freezes and digs in his pockets excitedly.
Ah. Now I'm interested!
Seth starts to chop at a tree, not taking the threat seriously.
t!8ball Does Emmett start chugging down the space rum Sanya passed him?
ðŸŽ± | Reply hazy try again,
> Zander
what
t!8ball Does Emmett start chugging down the space rum Sanya passed him?
ðŸŽ± | Most likely, Zander.
Emmett takes a swig of the rum, the effects of the alcohol helping him block out the pains from his lack of grass consumption.
Whooh yeah.
Sanya peers at Emmett from her book.
Are you getting drunk?
Warlord dropships often carry at least 200 soldiers...
The KYL unit's lights change to yellow, expressing a hint of fear.
Emmett shrugs, continuing to drink.
I don't think so.
Jim, trying to ignore the Mantis presence on the planet, decides to compare his augments to KYL300.
So, Kyle, do you even have any heat sensors?
Takes me a few drinks of this to get me even tipsy...
Emmett winks at Sanya.
I do, but the ship is too far away to properly scan it...
Jim sighs and pauses for a couple of seconds in thought.
Okay, we will wait then.
They would have sent something else if they wanted to kill us.
Want some, Sanya?
Emmett shakes his drink at her.
t!8ball Does Sanya get up and sit in another chair?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook good, Brakia.
Sanya rolls her eyes and finally gets off of Emmett, moving to another chair.
Oof.
I don't think they know we're here. But they will.
The world feels lighter now.
They are coming in our direction...
t!8ball Does the Mantis ship start violently shooting at the crew with spud guns?
ðŸŽ± | Without a doubt, PlasmaPerson.
And if this is a military place, then they would have high security...
Jim dodges a potato, it splatting on the ground at a high velocity.
Are those potatoes?!
AWESOME, FREE FOOD!
Seth attempts to catch a potato, running about.
I still feel deflated though...
Emmett starts to shiver, his muscles starting to tense up.
t!8ball Does Matthias slow his heart rate to 1 BPM?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, Enchantingtable2013.
Sanya doesn't pay Emmett any attention, more focused on her book.
I wonder what'sss happening outssside?
Garrick manages to catch a potato, it having been shot at the correct angle to enter his pocket.
Baked potatoes???
Garrick flies about the field, grabbing scraps of potatoes and pocketing them.
Potatoes are a main explosive in the Mantis arsenal...
KYL300 surprisingly doesn't move, not perceiving the potato storm as a threat just yet.
Chomsky dodge rolls away from the onslaught of potatoes.
SPUDS!
Emmett shudders and grimaces, the veins in his arms starting to pop out.
I might actually be turning now...
t!8ball Does Seth shoot the warship and make it crash on a small baby?
ðŸŽ± | My reply is no, Bagelwrecker.
Emmett, you might want to come out here, we got a situation.
And we also have some grass.
Emmett manages to bring his arm to his mouth, the strain in his voice apparent.
Who the FUCK are you talking to!?
They're dropping in soldiers!
t!choose KYL300 grabs everyone and run to the ship | KYL300 runs to the ship | KYL300 stands its ground
ðŸ¤” | ProfessorTree, I pick run to the ship!
KYL300 runs back to the ship in a panic.
I'm going back to the ship! I suggest you follow me!
Garrick flips the ships off.
HEY! MANTIS! PISS OFF!
Jim swerves around and watches the coward robot run off.
Hey, where do you're think you're going?
t!8ball Have the Manti ships dropped soldiers?
ðŸŽ± | Don't count on it, Bagelwrecker.
Chomsky scoffs.
Thanks a lot, coward!
Sanya puts down her book as KYL300 enters the room.
Oh, It'sss the robot...
Garrick smirks and hits his hands in satisfaction.
They'll go away now.
Emmett mutters into his comms, considering that the others are more focused on the Mantis ships.
It's called "The Crave", by Seth...
I guarantee it.
I need like, some grassy sustainance...
Emmett watches his other arm waver with more intensity.
More potatoes!
Seth grabs what he thinks is clean and sticks it into his mouth. He rubs his stomach in satisfaction.
I am standing here, there is no point in running.
Jim shrugs, not even bothering to dodge the spud rain.
Hundreds of soldiers are coming our way. We need to get out of here.
At least like ten pounds a semester...
That'sss alot of grasss.
Matthias walks into the lounge, unaware of the havoc occurring on the planet outside.
Hey guys, look at this cool tattoo that came out of nowhere!
What?
Sanya's head bolts towards Matthias as he enters.
Who the hell are you?
Emmett inhales, trying not to have an aneursym by Matthias's indifference.
I am literally dying here and you care about a tattoo, Math.
I'm the real OG, but I've been lowkey.
Matthias snaps his fingers in Emmett's direction with a beaky smile.
Yep.
Jim yells into the ship from the hatch.
Hey, Kyle, go turn yourself into a lawn mower or something!
Sanya tilts her head at Matthias in confusion by his slang.
What doesss that even mean?
Matthias puts his hands on his hips and puffs his chest out.
Ah, you uncultured swine.
Excuse me?
Jim is outside the ship, waiting for the arrival of the Mantis ship.
The most hip of avians know the code.
Matthias gyrates his hips.
t!8ball Does Emmett fall off the couch and attempt to get himself up?
ðŸŽ± | Yes, Zander.
Jim takes out a cigarette and lights it with a lighter.
Lawnmowers are probably the worst thing we can call lawn mowers...
Upon Emmett falling, Matthias tenses his eyes, staring at the poor goat.
Why don't we just drag him out to the grass?
Emmett pushes himself up in an attempt to get up, but at this point, he's a bit to weak to do even this.
Is there anything outside?
t!8ball Does the Mantis ship land?
ðŸŽ± | Ask again later, TheBlade.
There's a warlord dropship outside...
Chomsky smiles, his sunglasses reflecting the light directly back at the ship attacking them.
Just carnage.
Uh oh.
Matthias frowns.
t!8ball Does the Mantis ship land?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook not so good, TheBlade.
The Mantis are coming. Seth thinks it'll be a good idea to try and fight.
Cause I'm hungry, robo-bro!
With one final chop, Seth's finally able to chop down a tree, it making a huge thump outside.
Matthias jumps from the thump of the tree startling him.
I just got out of a mid-sleep journey to find my creator and there's already people dying?
What a vacation.
t!8ball Does Sanya leave the ship to see what's happening?
ðŸŽ± | Outlook not so good, Brakia.
Sanya frets over Emmett's condition.
You okay, Emmett?
Cigarette in mouth, Jim takes out his shotgun, readying it.
Everyone get out here, we are about to get some visitors!
Yes, he is.
Matthias prods Emmett with the talons on his leg.
Emmett swipes at Matthias's foot weakly.
I think I'm in a shitty position...
Totally not malnourished.
Sanya is anxious, her brow raising in worry.
What do you mean?
t!8ball Does Emmett start saying nonsense and hallucinates due to his condition?
ðŸŽ± | Very doubtful, PlasmaPerson.
Matthias shakes his head and shifts his focus to the glowing brand on his hand.
See, look at what my god gave me!
t!8ball Does Matthias blink from one side of the room to the other?
ðŸŽ± | Most likely, Enchantingtable2013.
Matthias laughs excitedly.
